tandaina:<br>
<br>
Magelo is a site that provides EQ players a place to show off their character's equipment and stats.<br>
<br>
You basically sign up, log in, and fill in the blanks (by using their drop-down menus) with what your character wears or has.  Then visitors who knows the URL that your character's info is stored on can see your stats, equipment, and click on the equipment's stats.  It's pretty interactive and easy to set up.  Most if not all EQ equipment are stored in their database for you equip your profile with.  (Minus SoL equipment I'm sure. :) )<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/">www.magelo.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I quit EQ before I discovered Magelo so I don't have a profile for my character as an example.  However, I know many people that posts on this board uses it.  Just click around on people's signature and I'm sure you'll find one and see what it's like.  <br>
<br>
My signature leads to my DAoC character's profile.  It's actually a really neat lil template that <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://daoc.catacombs.com">daoc.catacombs.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> set up.  You can plot out your character's stats and plan out where and how to allocate your points before you ding so you don't make a mistake.  For example, say you're 15th lvl and want to see how many points you'll have to spend at 20th lvl and want to plan out exactly which spells you want to have by then, you can do that.  You can also save it for private viewing or for the world to see. <p><CENTER>
